<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-22T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-22T17:00:00-05:00" n="649" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">865.30/51: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-22T23:00:00+01:00">October
                                    22, 1943—11 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 22—12:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3083. My 293 [<hi rend="italic">2933</hi>] October 10. I discussed
                            Italian warships in Balearics again with Jordana today. I said legal
                            status clear and Spain should release ships promptly. There were more
                            than 2,000 seamen involved and I was sure the Spanish authorities would
                            not want any trouble at Port Mahon. He said both he and Minister of
                            Marine greatly impressed by arguments set forth in my note 1444 of
                            October 12 (see my despatch 1441, October 12) and he hoped to reply very
                            speedily. I said I trusted the decision would be favorable and he
                            replied that our arguments were very strong.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>